  "ciliary_role": "Phosphorylates the centrosomal linker proteins C-  p1, Cep68 and Rootletin to promote centriole separation, and is involved in the development of left-right asymmetry by regulating balancing ciliogenesis and resorption (26493400). Phosphorylates Kif24, a depolymerising kinesin (26290419). Influences centrosome-anchored  organisation and promotes cilium disassembly at the onset of mitosis (22613497). NEK2 removes distal appendage components from the mother centriole, preventing cilia mainte nce during mitosis (32211891).",
